<subSubSection box="[199,993,331,358]" pageId="12" pageNumber="435" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1443,259,826]" box="[199,993,331,358]" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,331,357]" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the name of the 
<typeStatus box="[848,896,332,358]" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="435" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1443,259,826]" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,367,393]" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of the new species differs from all species considered in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walckenaer" authorityYear="1826" box="[1137,1241,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1137,1241,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Zodarion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by twisted RTA (
<figureCitation box="[160,262,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[182,1407,209,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[168,1419,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 12. Zodarion sharurensis sp. n. A–D male palp, ventral, retrolateral, prolateral and dorsal; E, F male and female habitus, dorsal. Arrow points to dorsal patellar spines. Scale bars = 0.2 mm, unless stated otherwise. Abbreviations: Br—base of retrolateral tibial apophysis, Ce—cymbial extension, Co—conductor, Eb—base of embolus, Em—embolus, Pe—posterior tegular extension, Ta—tegular apophysis, Te—ventral tegular extension, Tr—terminal part of retrolateral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683505/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
) (
<emphasis box="[289,320,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">vs.</emphasis>
uncoiled in other species), and the presence of retrolateral cymbial (
<emphasis box="[1116,1147,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Ce</emphasis>
) and tegular (
<emphasis box="[1312,1337,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Te</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1397,1427,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Pe</emphasis>
) extensions. The female of 
<taxonomicName authority="Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2022" authorityName="Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2022" box="[448,608,439,465]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sharurensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[448,608,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Z. sharurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[615,679,439,465]" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[615,679,439,465]" pageId="12" pageNumber="435" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has epigyne similar to those in 
<taxonomicName authority="Wunderlich, 1980" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="1980" box="[1036,1388,439,466]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abantense">
<emphasis box="[1036,1052,440,465]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Z</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1066,1180,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">abantense</emphasis>
Wunderlich, 1980
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Dunin &amp; Nenilin, 1897" authorityName="Dunin &amp; Nenilin" authorityYear="1897" box="[151,591,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talyschicum">
<emphasis box="[151,317,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Z. talyschicum</emphasis>
Dunin &amp; Nenilin, 1897
</taxonomicName>
by having round, widely separated receptacles and straight (i.e. uncoiled) copulatory ducts. It can be differentiated from both species by having receptacles separated by 3.3 diameters (
<emphasis box="[1406,1429,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">vs</emphasis>
. 2.7). Furthermore, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="1980" box="[436,583,547,573]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abantense">
<emphasis box="[436,583,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Z. abantense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs by fovea with parallel margins (
<emphasis box="[1079,1102,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">vs</emphasis>
. triangular) and distinct (i.e. well sclerotized) copulatory ducts visible through integument (
<emphasis box="[881,904,584,609]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">vs</emphasis>
. indistinct). It can also be diagnosed from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dunin &amp; Nenilin" authorityYear="1897" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talyschicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Z. talyschicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by wider epigynal fovea (2 times longer than wide 
<emphasis box="[863,886,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">vs</emphasis>
. 3 times longer than wide).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="438" pageId="12" pageNumber="435" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1443,259,826]" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,655,681]" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[577,677,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[182,1407,209,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[168,1419,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 12. Zodarion sharurensis sp. n. A–D male palp, ventral, retrolateral, prolateral and dorsal; E, F male and female habitus, dorsal. Arrow points to dorsal patellar spines. Scale bars = 0.2 mm, unless stated otherwise. Abbreviations: Br—base of retrolateral tibial apophysis, Ce—cymbial extension, Co—conductor, Eb—base of embolus, Em—embolus, Pe—posterior tegular extension, Ta—tegular apophysis, Te—ventral tegular extension, Tr—terminal part of retrolateral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683505/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Fig. 12E</figureCitation>
. Total length 1.90. Carapace 0.88 long, 0.70 wide. Eye sizes: AME: 0.08, ALE: 0.07, PME: 0.06, PLE: 0.05. Carapace, sternum, chelicerae, labium and maxillae yellowish brown. Legs slightly lighter than carapace, without annulations. Abdomen dorsally dark grayish and with pale median band; pale beige ventrally. Spinnerets uniformly pale beige. Measurements of legs: I: 2.82 (0.66, 0.31, 0.65, 0.67, 0.53), II: 2.52 (0.65, 0.29, 0.52, 0.59, 0.47), III: 2.42 (0.62, 0.30, 0.49, 0.59, 0.42), IV: 3.47 (0.88, 0.34, 0.79, 0.96, 0.50).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683503" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6683503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683503/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="435" startId="12.[151,250,1839,1863]" targetBox="[151,1436,849,1815]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1839,1935]" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,1839,1863]" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">FIGURE 11.</emphasis>
Epigyne and vulva of 
<taxonomicName authority="Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2022" authorityName="Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2022" box="[515,733,1839,1863]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sharurensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[515,733,1839,1863]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Zodarion sharurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[739,796,1839,1863]" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[739,796,1839,1863]" pageId="12" pageNumber="435" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
A, E macerated epigyne, ventral and lateral; B vulva, dorsal; C same, ventrolateral; D, F macerated epigyne, posterior; G intact epigyne, ventroposterior. Scale bars = 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: 
<emphasis box="[151,202,1911,1935]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Ah—</emphasis>
anterior hood, 
<emphasis box="[350,402,1911,1935]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Cd—</emphasis>
copulatory duct, 
<emphasis box="[573,624,1912,1935]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Fo—</emphasis>
fovea, 
<emphasis box="[693,745,1912,1935]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Oc—</emphasis>
copulatory opening, 
<emphasis box="[954,1003,1912,1935]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="435">Re—</emphasis>
receptacle.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683505" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6683505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683505/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="436" startId="13.[151,250,1909,1933]" targetBox="[182,1407,209,1867]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1909,2041]" pageId="13" pageNumber="436">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,1909,1933]" pageId="13" pageNumber="436">FIGURE 12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2022" authorityName="Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2022" box="[299,519,1909,1933]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="436" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sharurensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[299,519,1909,1933]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="436">Zodarion sharurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[528,588,1909,1933]" pageId="13" pageNumber="436">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[528,588,1909,1933]" pageId="13" pageNumber="436" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
